item.description:
To use the Ethernet functions you must include hackair_ethernet.h after hackair.h and Ethernet.h.
#include &lt;Ethernet.h&gt; #include &lt;hackair.h&gt; #include &lt;hackair_ethernet.h&gt;  Constructor hackAirEthernet(EthernetClient ethernet, char *token)
Creates a container class for the Ethernet functions
Parameters:
 ethernet: Ethernet shield&rsquo;s library client token: Pointer to the Authentication token used by the API  Usage:
// MAC Address for the ethernet shield // Some shields should have the MAC address printed on them byte mac[] = { 0xDE, 0xAD, 0xBE, 0xEF, 0xFE, 0xED }; // Initialize the Ethernet libraries EthernetClient client; hackAirEthernet hackAirNet(client, &quot;AUTHORIZATION TOKEN&quot;); // Write your API key here  Method int sendData(hackAirData &amp;data)
